Al Jazeera reported the draft Iran peace deal, which reportedly includes:

🔻Ending hostilities (including in Lebanon);

🔻Releasing billions in frozen Iranian funds;

🔻Easing the U.S. naval presence around Hormuz;

🔻And pulling U.S. forces farther from Iran.

“Both sides would then get 30 days — extendable by mutual agreement — to finalize a nuclear deal, while Iran and Oman negotiate transit and control arrangements for the Strait of Hormuz.”
